public class FormulaOutputFormat
extends java.lang.Object

Defines how to represent the different operators. Provides a default implementation in NuSMV-like style.

setDefault

public void setDefault()
Defines a base interpretation of symbols for TFOL: and, or, not, implies => &, |, !, -> Existential and Universal quantifiers are expressed as Ex. and Ax. AlwaysFuture, AlwaysPast Always => G, H, H G SometimeFuture, SometimePast, Sometime => F, O, O F NextFuture, NextPast, Until, Since => X, Y, U, S All symbols are in Prefix notation except for Until and Since. Only the following are surrounded by parenthesis: And, Or, Implication, Until and Since Note: This interpretation is derived from NuSMV notation.
